guisubmenu
Element


guisubmenu
&guisubmenu.purpose;


&guisubmenu.synopsis.gen;
Description



The name of a submenu in a graphical user interface is identified by 
the GUISubmenu element.  A submenu is a
menu invoked from another menu that leads either to terminal items
(GUIMenuItems) or additional submenus.


Processing expectations


&format.inline; &pexp.moreinfo;




&guisubmenu.parents.gen;
&guisubmenu.children.gen;

Attributes

moreinfo



If MoreInfo is set to RefEntry,
it implies that a RefEntry exists which further describes the
GUISubMenu.





